Sentencas: Low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC, 300-600 degrees C) is one of the hot areas in recent fuel cell developments.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: In order to develop high performance LTSOFCs, compatible electrodes are highly demanded.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: We used NANOCOFC (nanocomposites for advanced fuel cell technology) approach to develop nanocomposite electrodes based on metal oxides Ni-Cu -Zn-oxide and samarium doped ceria (SDC).
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: It was found that the materials consist of individual metal oxide and SDC phase, indicating the material as a composite with a homogenous distribution for all constituent components.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: Highly homogenous distribution of the particles enhanced the catalyst function for electrode applications in LTSOFC devices.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: We constructed the devices using the SDC-carbonate nanocomposite (NSDC) as the electrolyte and above as prepared composite as electrodes in a symmetrical configuration.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: We found that the prepared composite electrodes had good catalytic function for both H-2 and O-2, to prove its anode and cathode functions.
Titulo: Nanocomposite electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells using the ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes

Sentencas: Based on the material properties, the LTSOFC devices have reached a power output more than 730 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C. Copyright (C) 2011, Hydrogen Energy Publications, LLC.
